        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): guard formatAuditList against non-string items to prevent handshake trim crash (#90654)",
        "body": "## Summary\nCLI write commands (`openclaw message send`, `broadcast`, `probe`) crash the gateway WebSocket handshake with `TypeError: Cannot read properties of null/undefined (reading 'trim')` when the device pairing state contains non-string entries in roles/scopes arrays.\n\nThe root cause is unguarded `.trim()` calls on array items in the connect audit path. `formatAuditList` in `message-handler.ts` logs role/scope upgrades, and `mergeRoles`/`mergeScopes` in `device-pairing.ts` compute approved effective roles/scopes. When legacy or malformed pairing data reaches these helpers, the unguarded `.trim()` throws and the socket is closed before the handshake completes.\n\n## Changes\n- `src/gateway/server/ws-connection/message-handler.ts`: Extract `formatAuditList` to module-level, add `typeof item === \"string\"` guard before `.trim()`.\n- `src/infra/device-pairing.ts`: Add `typeof` guards in `mergeRoles` and `mergeScopes` to skip non-string array entries.\n- `src/gateway/server/ws-connection/message-handler.post-connect-health.test.ts`: Add regression tests for `formatAuditList`.\n- `src/infra/device-pairing.test.ts`: Add regression test for malformed roles/scopes arrays in pairing records.\n- `scripts/repro/issue-90654-gateway-handshake-trim-crash.mts`: Helper-level reproduction for `formatAuditList`.\n- `scripts/repro/issue-90654-gateway-handshake-trim-crash-websocket.mts`: Standalone WebSocket reproduction that starts a real gateway, loads malformed pairing state, and completes a connect handshake.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: A real WebSocket gateway connect handshake no longer crashes when persisted device pairing state contains non-string roles/scopes entries.\n- **Real environment tested**: Linux x64, Node v24.15.0, local OpenClaw source checkout, running a real `startGatewayServer` with an actual WebSocket client (no Vitest mocks).\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n  - `node --import tsx scripts/repro/issue-90654-gateway-handshake-trim-crash-websocket.mts`\n- **Evidence after fix**: Terminal output from real Node.js runtime:\n  ```text\n  === Reproduction for issue #90654 (WebSocket handshake) ===\n  Temp state dir: /tmp/openclaw-repro-90654-ws-JIp1sn\n  Starting gateway on port 42425...\n  Gateway started.\n  Connecting WebSocket to port 42425...\n  [ws] open\n  [ws] message: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"connect.challenge\",\"payload\":{\"nonce\":\"3d6539c6-8f52-438b-9651-8735786a07aa\",\"ts\":1781237739591}}\n  Got challenge nonce: 3d6539c6-8f52-438b-9651-8735786a07aa\n  Sending connect with role: operator scopes: [ 'write' ]\n  [ws] message: {\"type\":\"res\",\"id\":\"87bd0012-6abf-4779-97e5-234b73c7448e\",\"ok\":false,\"error\":{\"code\":\"NOT_PAIRED\",\"message\":\"pairing required: device is asking for a higher role than currently approved\",...}}\n  [ws] close: 1008 pairing required: device is asking for a higher role than currently approved (requestId: ...)\n  PASS: Gateway WebSocket handshake did not crash with malformed pairing state.\n  ```\n- **Observed result after fix**: The gateway receives the connect request, logs the role/scope upgrade audit (`roleFrom=<none> roleTo=operator scopesFrom=read scopesTo=write`), and responds with a structured `NOT_PAIRED` error instead of crashing. The socket closes with code 1008 and a clear pairing-required reason. No `TypeError` is thrown.\n- **What was not tested**: Live multi-hop network or TLS-terminated gateway; the proof uses loopback WebSocket only.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server/ws-connection/message-handler.post-connect-health.test.ts --run` → 84 passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/device-pairing.test.ts --run` → 58 passed\n- `npx oxlint --import-plugin --config .oxlintrc.json src/gateway/server/ws-connection/message-handler.ts src/infra/device-pairing.ts src/infra/device-pairing.test.ts` → clean\n- `node --import tsx scripts/repro/issue-90654-gateway-handshake-trim-crash-websocket.mts` → PASS\n- `node --import tsx scripts/repro/issue-90654-gateway-handshake-trim-crash.mts` → PASS\n\n🤖 AI-assisted PR\n",
        "branch": "fix/90654-gateway-handshake-trim-crash",
